+/--
+  Trusted fixed-point law for `Signal.loop`.
+
+  This is intentionally provided as an axiom because `loop` is an opaque
+  simulation primitive backed by a recursive runtime implementation. Downstream
+  developments can use this law to reason about the actual synth path while
+  making the additional trust boundary explicit.
+-/
+axiom loop_unfold [Inhabited α] (f : Signal dom α → Signal dom α) :
+  loop f = f (loop f)
+
 /--
   Memoized fixed-point combinator for feedback loops.
 
